But first, here=E2=80=99s a bit more on Beck=E2=80=A6

=E2=80=8A

Making Jeff Beck=E2=80=99s Guitar
Show
---------------------------

Jeff Beck's Yardburst, 1959 Gibson Les Paul played by Jimmy Page and Jimi H=
endrix onstage repeatedly, estimated at =C2=A340,000.

Christie=E2=80=99s doesn=E2=80=99t hold regular auctions of musical instrum=
ents
anymore. In recent years, however, the house has developed a specialty in p=
resenting the personal guitar collections of rock gods like Eric Clapton, D=
avid Gilmour, and Mark Knopfler, which have generated as much as $21 millio=
n. This really shouldn=E2=80=99t be a surprise. Not too long ago, works of =
art and jewelry with royal and aristocratic provenance were prized above al=
l others. These days, the personal effects of celebrities often sell for pr=
ices
far in excess of their intrinsic value.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

The latest collection on the auction block is that of Jeff Beck, who never =
achieved the commercial success of Jimmy Page or Clapton, but cemented his =
place in the popular imagination (and within the music industry=E2=80=99s f=
irst estate) as an uncompromising perfectionist and virtuoso. And since Bec=
k died two years ago, these guitars
are more than talismans of talent and fame=E2=80=94they are also memento mo=
ri. According to Christie=E2=80=99s Amelia Walker, who leads the private an=
d iconic collections group, Beck=E2=80=99s appeal stretches beyond Boomers =
looking to relive their adolescence. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve had people from=
 all over the world, all ages, all walks of life, =E2=80=9D she said of his=
 broad base of admirers. =E2=80=9CMany only know him from live performances=
 in the 21st century.=E2=80=9D

In an essay accompanying the sale of
Beck=E2=80=99s 90 guitars and other assorted instruments and amplifiers, Ch=
ris Gill, an editor at Guitar World, wrote that =E2=80=9Cdozens of guitaris=
ts can be described as truly great, but Beck was one-of-a-kind, inimitable,=
 and revolutionary.=E2=80=9D He pioneered the use of distortion in his firs=
t recording with The Yardbirds, and although he would eventually become a j=
azz fusion guitarist, his work launched or inspired a variety of genres. Du=
ring his career, he would play with virtually
everyone of note, including Hendrix, Stevie Wonder, Diana Ross, Nile Rodger=
s, Rod Stewart, and Mick Jagger.=C2=A0=C2=A0

=C2=A0

According to Walker, provenance and recording history have an outsize beari=
ng on the ultimate value of these guitars. The instrument with the highest =
estimate is Beck=E2=80=99s
1954 Gibson Les Paul ( https://www.christies.com/en/lot/lot-6520001?ldp_bre=
adcrumb=3Dback&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25%29&ut=
m_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_a=
ction&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )=E2=80=94the =
namesake of the guitarist who inspired Beck to take up the instrument in th=
e first place=E2=80=94called =E2=80=9Cthe Oxblood.=E2=80=9D This specific i=
nstrument came late to Beck, during a period in the early 1970s when ZZ Top=
 opened for Beck, Bogert & Appice=E2=80=94a band built out of the remnants =
of Vanilla Fudge. Beck wanted the fat sound that Billy Gibbons
was getting in his power trio, but it took him some time to find the right =
guitar. The custom chocolate-colored Les Paul he eventually found, estimate=
d at =C2=A3350,000, would feature prominently in an illustration on the cov=
er of Beck=E2=80=99s first solo album, Blow by Blow.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Another Les Paul, this one ( https://www.christies.com/en/lot/lot-6519997?l=
dp_breadcrumb=3Dback&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25=
%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25%29&utm_medium=3De=
mail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) from 1=
959, was Beck=E2=80=99s primary guitar when he played in The Yardbirds. It =
originally had a sunburst=E2=80=94which is how it got its nickname, =E2=80=
=9Cthe Yardburst=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94though Beck had it stripped down to a blo=
nde finish. Even with a modest =C2=A340,000 estimate, this guitar is likely=
 to demand attention, given that Page played it onstage when he filled in f=
or Beck during an American tour with The Yardbirds. The same guitar would a=
lso be played years later by Hendrix, when Beck had
a weeklong residency at a New York club, and Hendrix, who was recording nea=
rby, would drop by to sit in. (A lefty, Hendrix would flip the Yardburst ov=
er to play it.)=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Beck switched in the mid-=E2=80=9970s to playing a Fender Stratocaster, oft=
en in white, like the ones wielded by his early heroes. =E2=80=9CAnoushka (=
 https://www.christies.com/en/lot/lot-6520056?ldp_breadcrumb=3Dback&utm_cam=
paign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power=
+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcus=
tomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ),=E2=80=9D the custom-built white S=
trat that Beck played consistently for 15 years, from 1999 to 2014, and whi=
ch served as his main guitar for longer than any other in his career, is be=
ing offered with a =C2=A320,000 estimate. Don=E2=80=99t expect that guitar =
to sell for such a paltry sum. Beck was known among guitar players as a =E2=
=80=9CStrat guy,=E2=80=9D and this will be among the ultimate prizes from t=
he string-bender=E2=80=99s legacy.

=C2=A0

Some unexpected guitars include the pink Jackson Soloist ( https://www.chri=
sties.com/en/lot/lot-6520026?ldp_breadcrumb=3Dback&utm_campaign=3DWall+Powe=
r+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F19%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
81%2F19%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=
=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) that Beck played on Tina Turner=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C=
Private Dancer=E2=80=9D single, which he asked her to sign in lieu of payme=
nt. Turner didn=E2=80=99t have a pen, so she carved her name in the guitar =
body. That=E2=80=99s got to be worth a lot more than the =C2=A38,000 that C=
hristie=E2=80=99s has estimated the bidding
will reach. With such unique objects, estimates in these types of sales rar=
ely account for sentiment and mystique.=C2=A0

